Cell.Text: [S] S|Where did you learn of that? Who have you been talking to?
[S] Where did you learn of a Shout used to defeat Alduin?

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroTopic: I need to learn the Shout used to defeat Alduin.

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> The Blades! Of course. They specialize in meddling in matters they barely understand. Their reckless arrogance knows no bounds.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroA2New: It was recorded on Alduin's Wall.

Cell.Text: Yes. For matters of such gravity, we need to know where you stand. Or who you stand with.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroA1New: Does it matter?

Cell.Text: [S] Ah, the prophecy. Be wary of prophecy. Some are meant as a guide. Some as a warning. Are you sure you can tell one from the other?

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroB3: The prophecy says I'm the only one who can defeat Alduin.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> It was created by those who had lived under the unimaginable cruelty of Alduin's Dragon Cult. | Their whole lives were consumed with hatred for dragons, and they poured all their anger and hatred into this Shout. | When you learn a Shout, you take it into your very being. In a sense, you become the Shout. | In order to learn and use this Shout, you will be taking this evil into yourself.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirDragonrendBadTopic: What's so bad about the Dragonrend Shout?

Cell.Text: Perhaps not. But this Shout was used once before, was it not? And here we are again. | Have you considered that Alduin was not meant to be defeated? | Those who overthrew him in ancient times only postponed the day of reckoning, they did not stop it. | If the world is meant to end, so be it. Let it end and be reborn.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirDefeatAlduinTopic: Is there another way to defeat Alduin?

Cell.Text: What do you have against the Blades?

[S] <<Shared>> The Blades were born of dragon-hating crusaders. They still carry that legacy although they may not remember from whence it came. | They carried out a genocide of dragons when they first came to Tamriel, and now they will do it again, with your help.
Not hate. Distrust and fear. The Blades have always sought to turn the Dragonborn away from the path of wisdom.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirHateBladesTopic: Why do you hate the Blades?

Cell.Text: That may be what you are here for, Dragonborn. | But stopping Alduin is one thing. Helping you wipe out dragons again is quite another. | Dragons are part of the natural order of the world. The Blades thought to change the order to suit themselves, by wiping out the dragons. | But again, we see that the natural order will be restored, one way or another. | Perhaps we would have dragon allies against Alduin if the ancient Blades had not acted so arrogantly.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirStopDragonsTopic: The dragons are terrorizing Skyrim. Don't you think they need to be stopped?

Cell.Text: G|If you wish to stand alone, so be it. If you wish for our help, you'll answer my question.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroA1B1: Who I stand with is my business.

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> The Blades! Of course. They specialize in meddling in matters they barely understand. Their reckless arrogance knows no bounds.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroA4: Fine. The Blades helped me find out about it.

Cell.Text: They have always sought to turn the Dragonborn from the path of wisdom. | Have you learned nothing from us? Would you simply be a tool in the hands of the Blades, to be used for their own purposes?

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroB1

Cell.Text: Do not be so sure about that. Beware - the Blades may claim to serve the Dragonborn, but they do not. They never have. | As for me, I kept from you only what you were not yet ready to know. Are still not ready to know, as your question reveals.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroC3New: At least the Blades aren't keeping secrets from me.

Cell.Text: [S] Forgive me. I was... intemperate. I allowed my emotions to cloud my judgment. Master Einarth reminded me of my duty. | The decision whether or not to help you is not mine to make.
G|I have given my answer. Go and reconsider your course.
So the Blades have survived yet another disaster of their own making, and continue to meddle in things they do not understand.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirExclusiveTopic: I need to learn the Shout used to defeat Alduin.

Cell.Text: S|Only Paarthurnax, the master of our order, can answer that question, if he so chooses.
To get the answers you seek, you must travel to the top of the mountain and speak to our master, Paarthurnax.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirDragonrendExclusiveTopic: If the Shout is lost, how can I defeat Alduin?

Cell.Text: [S] You weren't ready. You still aren't ready. | But thanks to the Blades, you now have questions that only Paarthurnax can answer.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirPaarthurnaxA3: I need to speak to Paarthurnax, then.

Cell.Text: [S] He lives in seclusion on the very peak of the mountain. | He speaks to us only rarely, and never to outsiders. Being allowed to see him is a great privilege.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirPaarthurnaxA2: Why haven't I met Paarthurnax yet?

Cell.Text: [S] G|Only those whose Voice is strong can find the path. Come. We will teach you a Shout to open the way to Paarthurnax.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirExclusiveEndTopic: How do I get to the top of the mountain to see him?

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> The Blades! Of course. They specialize in meddling in matters they barely understand. Their reckless arrogance knows no bounds.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroA3New: The Blades helped me find out about it.

Cell.Text: No. I cannot teach it to you because I do not know it.

Let it end and be reborn.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroC1: The Blades just want to defeat Alduin. Don't you?

Cell.Text: [S] No, no, of course not. Forgive me, Dragonborn. I have been intemperate with you. | But heed my warning - the Blades may say they serve the Dragonborn, but they do not. They never have.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroC2: The Blades are helping me. I'm not their puppet.

Cell.Text: G|No. Not now. Not until you return to the path of wisdom.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroD1: So you won't help me?

Cell.Text: Do not confuse inaction with indifference. Often the wisest course is to wait and watch events unfold, until the time to act is clear. | The Blades have never followed that path, of course.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroD2: I'm sure Alduin would be glad if everyone had that attitude.

Cell.Text: Those who are ignorant find the Way of the Voice easy to ridicule. | This is why so few follow it, and why the world is as it is.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirIntroD3: That's exactly what Delphine warned me you'd say.

Cell.Text: I cannot teach you the Shout, because I do not know it.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirExclusive2EntryTopic: I need to learn the Shout used to defeat Alduin.

Cell.Text: It is called "Dragonrend", but its Words of Power are unknown to us. | We do not regret this loss. Dragonrend holds no place within the Way of the Voice.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirExclusive2Continue

Cell.Text: He is our leader. He surpasses us all in his mastery of the Way of the Voice.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirPaarthurnaxA1: Who is Paarthurnax?

Cell.Text: But not Dragonrend. The knowledge of that Shout was lost in the time before history began. | Perhaps only its creators ever knew it. But I am not the one to speak of it to you.

Node.Caption: MQ204ArngeirDragonrendA1: I thought you knew all the Words of Power.
